Definition: a stimulant drug that is chemically related to mescaline and amphetamine and is used illicitly for its euphoric and hallucinogenic effects
Example: it was formerly used in psychotherapy but in 1985 it was declared illegal in the United States; MDMA is often used at parties because it enables partygoers to remain active for long periods of time
Synonyms: MDMA, club_drug, a, stimulant, drug, that, is, chemically, related, to, mescaline, and, amphetamine, used, illicitly, for, its, euphoric, hallucinogenic, effects, it, was, formerly, in, psychotherapy, but, declared, illegal, the, United, States, often, at, parties, because, enables, partygoers, remain, active, long, periods, of, time
Category: noun.artifact
